---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Doctor of Education (EdD) | Doctoral College UK" description="DCUK's EdD programme for education professionals — three years part-time, online with residentials, specialist supervision. £7,500 per year.">

  <section class="bg-surface border-b border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">Programme</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Doctor of Education</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-accent font-medium mb-4">EdD &mdash; Three years part-time &mdash; £7,500 per year</p>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted max-w-2xl">The DCUK EdD is designed for professionals whose work is rooted in education — from classroom teachers and school leaders to further education practitioners, educational policy professionals, and university educators. It is a doctorate shaped by the distinctive intellectual traditions of educational research.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Overview -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-12">
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">3 Years</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Part-time, designed for working educators</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">£7,500/yr</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Total £22,500. Employer and professional body funding options available.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">Education Focus</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Specialist supervisors with deep expertise in education research and practice</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">Who It's For</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Built for Education Professionals</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">The EdD at DCUK is for anyone who works in education and wants to investigate a significant question through doctoral research. You do not need to be a school teacher — our EdD community includes further education leaders, educational psychologists, university academics, curriculum designers, Ofsted inspectors, and policy advisers.</p>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">What connects EdD researchers is a commitment to improving educational practice, policy, or outcomes — and a readiness to do so through rigorous, evidence-based inquiry rather than professional intuition alone.</p>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Teachers, school leaders, and headteachers</li>
            <li>Further and higher education practitioners</li>
            <li>Educational policy and research professionals</li>
            <li>Local authority and MAT leaders</li>
            <li>International education professionals</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">Entry Requirements</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">What We Look For</h2>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="card">
              <h3 class="font-semibold mb-1">Academic Qualifications</h3>
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">Master's degree at Merit or Distinction in education, educational leadership, or a closely related field. Applicants from other disciplines with strong professional portfolios in education may be considered.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <h3 class="font-semibold mb-1">Professional Experience</h3>
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">Significant professional experience in an education-related role. Senior practitioners with a track record in educational leadership, policy, or practice are particularly welcome to apply.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <h3 class="font-semibold mb-1">Research Proposal</h3>
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">A preliminary proposal of 1,500–2,000 words setting out your research focus, its educational significance, and an indication of your preferred methodological approach.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Structure -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-y border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Programme Structure</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Three Years of Structured Doctoral Development</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="text-xl font-bold text-accent mb-3">Year 1</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Conceptual Foundations</h3>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>Philosophy of Educational Research</li>
            <li>Educational Research Design and Methods</li>
            <li>Developing the Literature Review</li>
            <li>Positionality and Research Ethics in Education</li>
            <li>Research Proposal Development</li>
            <li>Supervision meetings (minimum 8/year)</li>
            <li>Two EdD residential weekends</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="text-xl font-bold text-accent mb-3">Year 2</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Inquiry in Practice</h3>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>Advanced Qualitative Methods for Education</li>
            <li>Fieldwork and data collection</li>
            <li>Data analysis workshops</li>
            <li>Annual Review milestone</li>
            <li>Peer research presentation</li>
            <li>Supervision meetings (minimum 8/year)</li>
            <li>Two EdD residential weekends</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="text-xl font-bold text-accent mb-3">Year 3</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Thesis and Examination</h3>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>Thesis writing supported by supervisor feedback</li>
            <li>Academic Writing for Education Researchers</li>
            <li>Pre-submission panel review</li>
            <li>Thesis submission (60,000–80,000 words)</li>
            <li>Viva voce examination</li>
            <li>Award of EdD</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Modules -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Taught Modules</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Developing Your Research Capability</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8">The EdD combines taught modules with supervised independent research. Modules are delivered online through our learning platform, with live sessions scheduled to accommodate working professionals.</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Philosophy of Educational Research</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">An introduction to the philosophical foundations of educational research — ontology, epistemology, and the implications of different paradigms for research design and methodology.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Educational Research Design</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Systematic coverage of research design in education: case study, action research, ethnography, survey methods, narrative inquiry, and mixed methods approaches.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Ethics and Positionality in Educational Research</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">The ethical dimensions of educational research, with particular attention to insider research, working with children and young people, and institutional power dynamics.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Advanced Qualitative Methods</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Detailed coverage of qualitative data collection and analysis methods used in educational research, including thematic analysis, IPA, grounded theory, and narrative methods.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Academic Writing for Education Researchers</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Developing the academic writing and argumentation skills required for doctoral-level scholarship — from argument construction to the conventions of educational research writing.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Leadership in Educational Systems</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">An optional specialist module examining contemporary theory and research on educational leadership — from school leadership to system-level governance and policy.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-t border-border py-16 px-6 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Take the next step in education</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8">If you have a research question about education that you have been sitting with — about leadership, practice, policy, or learning — the EdD is where you address it rigorously.</p>
      <div class="flex gap-4 justify-center flex-wrap">
        <a href="/apply" class="btn-primary">Apply now</a>
        <a href="/connect" class="btn-outline">Speak to us first</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
